Class GymManager

java.lang.Object
project1.GymManager
public class GymManager extends Object
User Interface class to process the command lines entered o the IDE console and display the results on the console. Starts with " Gym Manager running...‚Äù and ends with "Gym Manager terminated."
Author:
Songyuan Zhang, Robert Jimenez

      Create a GymManager object. Initialize one MemberDatabase object and three FitnessClass objects for each Pilates, Spinning, and Cardio. fitness classes.

  • Method Details

    • checkValidCalendarDate

      private boolean checkValidCalendarDate(Member member)
      Check valid calendar date for member's date of birth or expiration date. Extracts the dates from member and use isValid method from Dateclass to check whether date is valid.
      Parameters:
      member - the member with date of birth or expiration date to check valid calendar date.
      Returns:
      true if the date is a valid calendar date, false otherwise.

    • checkTodayOrFutureDate

      private boolean checkTodayOrFutureDate(Date date)
      Check the date is today or future date. Compare the results against today's date.
      Parameters:
      date - the date to check it is today or future date.
      Returns:
      true if the date is today or future date, false otherwise.

    • checkValidGymLocation

      private boolean checkValidGymLocation(String inputString)
      Check whether the input location is a valid gym location. Check if the location exists in Location enum class.
      Parameters:
      inputString - the string of the name of the gym location
      Returns:
      true if the date is today or future date, false otherwise.

    • addMember

      private void addMember(String[] results, int countTokenNumber, String commandLineString)
      Add a valid member into the MemberDatabase. Add a member who has valid date of birth, age, member expiration date, and gym location. Correpsonds to the A command.
      Parameters:
      results - string array that contains the command line instruction tokens.
      countTokenNumber - count for the number of tokens of the command line instruction.
      commandLineString - string of the original command line instruction.

    • cancelMember

      private void cancelMember(String[] results, int countTokenNumber, String commandLineString)
      Cancel a member from the MemberDatabase. Remove a member who exists in the MemberDatabase. Corresponds to the R command.
      Parameters:
      results - string array that contains the command line instruction tokens.
      countTokenNumber - count for the number of tokens of the command line instruction.
      commandLineString - string of the original command line instruction.

    • listMember

      private void listMember(String[] results, int countTokenNumber, String commandLineString)
      Print all members from the MemberDatabase. Display the list of members in the database without sorting (current order in the array.) Corresponds to the P command.
      Parameters:
      results - string array that contains the command line instruction tokens.
      countTokenNumber - count for the number of tokens of the command line instruction.
      commandLineString - string of the original command line instruction.

    • listMemberByCounty

      private void listMemberByCounty(String[] results, int countTokenNumber, String commandLineString)
      Print all members from the MemberDatabase order by the county names and then the zip codes. If the locations are in the same county, ordered by the zip codes. Corresponds to the PC command.
      Parameters:
      results - string array that contains the command line instruction tokens.
      countTokenNumber - count for the number of tokens of the command line instruction.
      commandLineString - string of the original command line instruction.

    • listMemberByName

      private void listMemberByName(String[] results, int countTokenNumber, String commandLineString)
      Print the list of members in the database ordered by the members‚Äô last names and then first names. If two members have the same last name, ordered by the first name. Corresponds to the PN command.
      Parameters:
      results - string array that contains the command line instruction tokens.
      countTokenNumber - count for the number of tokens of the command line instruction.
      commandLineString - string of the original command line instruction.

    • listMemberByExpirationDate

      private void listMemberByExpirationDate(String[] results, int countTokenNumber, String commandLineString)
      Print the list of members in the database ordered by the expiration dates. If two expiration dates are the same, their order doesn‚Äôt matter. Corresponds to the PD command.
      Parameters:
      results - string array that contains the command line instruction tokens.
      countTokenNumber - count for the number of tokens of the command line instruction.
      commandLineString - string of the original command line instruction.

    • printNonEmptyStudentList

      private void printNonEmptyStudentList()
      Print the fitness class schedule together with students' information. Called by listFitnessClassSchedule method if the student lists in classes are not empty.

    • listFitnessClassSchedule

      private void listFitnessClassSchedule(String[] results, int countTokenNumber, String commandLineString)
      Print the fitness class schedule. A fitness class shall include the fitness class name, instructor‚Äôs name, the time of the class, and the list of members who have already checked in today. Corresponds to the S command.
      Parameters:
      results - string array that contains the command line instruction tokens.
      countTokenNumber - count for the number of tokens of the command line instruction.
      commandLineString - string of the original command line instruction.

    • checkInSpecificFitnessClass

      private boolean checkInSpecificFitnessClass(String className, Member member)
      Check into a fitness class for a member for time conflict with other fitness classes. Called by checkInFitnessClass method to perform the check in actin after all the validities has been verified at the checkInFitnessClass method.
      Parameters:
      className - string that shows the name of the class that the new member wants to check in.
      member - the member who wants to check into a specific class.
      Returns:
      true if check in is successful, false otherwise.

    • checkTimeConflict

      private boolean checkTimeConflict(String className, Member member)
      Check for time conflict with other fitness classes. Called by checkInFitnessClass method to check for time conflict with other fitness classes for a member.
      Parameters:
      className - string that shows the name of the class that the member wants to check in.
      member - the member who wants to check into a specific class.
      Returns:
      true if there is a time conflict, false otherwise.

    • checkExistanceInDatabase

      private boolean checkExistanceInDatabase(Member member)
      Check whether a member exists in the MemberDatabase. Called by checkInFitnessClass method to verify if the member exists in the MemberDatabase.
      Parameters:
      member - the member who wants to check into a specific class.
      Returns:
      true if member is already in the database, false otherwise.

    • checkInFitnessClass

      private void checkInFitnessClass(String[] results, int countTokenNumber, String commandLineString)
      Check into a fitness class. A member checks into a fitness class: Pilates, Spinning, or Cardio. Checks whether the member exists in the class, the date of birth is invalid, the fitness class exist or not, whether there is a time conflict with other fitness classes, or whether a member has already check into the class. Corresponds to the C command.
      Parameters:
      results - an array of strings that contains the command line instruction tokens.
      countTokenNumber - count for the number of tokens of the command line instruction.
      commandLineString - string of the original command line instruction.

    • dropSpecificFitnessClass

      private boolean dropSpecificFitnessClass(String className, Member member)
      Drop a member from a specific fitness class. Called by dropFitnessClass method to perform the action of dropping the member from the class: Pilates, Spinning, or Cardio fitness class.
      Parameters:
      className - the class name that the member wants to drop from
      member - the member who wants to drop from the fitness class.
      Returns:
      true if member is successfully dropped from the class, false otherwise.

    • dropFitnessClass

      private void dropFitnessClass(String[] results, int countTokenNumber, String commandLineString)
      Drop a member from a specific fitness class. Drop the fitness classes after the member checked in to a class. Corresponds to the D command.
      Parameters:
      results - an array of strings that contains the command line instruction tokens.
      countTokenNumber - count for the number of tokens of the command line instruction.
      commandLineString - string of the original command line instruction.

    • checkQCommand

      private boolean checkQCommand(String[] results, int countTokenNumber, String commandLineString)
      Stop the program execution. Display "Gym Manager terminated." Corresponds to the Q command.
      Parameters:
      results - an array of strings that contains the command line instruction tokens.
      countTokenNumber - count for the number of tokens of the command line instruction.
      commandLineString - string of the original command line instruction.
      Returns:
      true if the command is valid and program can be terminated, false otherwise

    • run

      public void run()
      Run the GymManager to receive and execute command line instructions. Use scanner to continuously take in command line instructions. Terminates when the Q command is received.
